                <note rend="inline" type="source">368.117/102: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hall</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-04-11T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 11, 1921—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>36. Meaning of last sentence of your 50 April 6, 6 p.m. not clear. Ascertain and
                    report specific classes to which assurances heretofore given by Greek Government
                    apply.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
